    "children": [
      {
        "type": "email",
        "html": "<p>Utilities shut off nearly six million people’s power for failure to pay since 2020 — and Florida has seen more shutoffs than most states, since several of the worst power-company offenders operate there. But as we note in <a href=\"__GHOST_URL__/desantis-lets-electric-companies-hide-their-dirty-work/?utm_source=newsletter-email&amp;utm_medium=link&amp;utm_campaign=newsletter-article\">today’s featured story</a>, we no longer know how many struggling Floridians are being left powerless, because Gov. Ron DeSantis and his Republican colleagues allowed electric utilities to stop disclosing shutoffs — after industry interests flooded their coffers with cash.</p>"
      },
